But yeah.,.. hospital... Take me back
Is it strange that I associate so many good things with being in hospital? I know it's not, because I spent a lot of stints there so obviously had good and bad experiences
I also remember getting visitors when I was in the ward. That was awesome. And sometimes family from out of town or interstate would mail me cards.
Hospital feels safe to me though, especially the children's wards. It just... Feels like permission to be unwell I guess? Permission to just be?

I legitimately knew most of the staff in the paed ward as a kid, so many left as I got older and filtered out. I think about some of them often, barely remember their faces or names, but they all felt like family to me and I hope they're doing well.
The nurses took me on their knees and brought me icecream and jelly (yuck I hated the combo but was too appreciative to care) and spooned it into my mouth as I sobbed while they rang my mum
Especially when one of my most memorable hospital experiences was as a 6 year old crying for my mum to come back to the hospital as she'd gone home to sleep and I woke without her scared.
It's such a bizarre feeling.
I want the near silent beeps and whirrs, the faint glow of many lights. I want to doze in and out of sleep, I want to stir as a nurse takes my temperature, and I want to fall straight back to sleep.

I feel pretty terrified to do much of anything right now. Part of its because of the load I know it would be on my body and the payback for that. Partially because I feel like, more than ever, hopes and plans are gonna be quashed.
I can't articulate what I want to get out of me... I know I can't and have never been able to control anything, but I feel like the small amount of things I could plan for and do... Are... Pointless
But... I can only control myself, and I do a pretty piss poor job of that half the time, especially when I'm unwell.

I didn't tell myself that this year. Part of me felt relief in the sense that... Well... I can't let myself down now at least??? It was comforting for a few days. Maybe I'm giving myself a break in saying that? Lessening expectations for myself?
I know it's kinda an unrealistic thing to "promise" yourself, but I guess its a thing that kinda kept me going.

Every year I have told myself "this is the year it gets better for you" and every year I have tried, every year I've been let down in some form, something has happened (sometimes good in hindsight, but painful at the time) to crush that
But I don't want to go back there. I don't want to live there. I really really do not want to live there anymore and I want all of this to stop.

I've been "here", traumatised, so MANY times that I just. I'm exhausted to the core from the fight and I don't want to fight, but I'm so scared that if I stop fighting that in going to get really really unwell. I've let myself taste it on the days that I've needed to

I feel this absolute white hot, super saiyan level pure rage whenever I realise I'm "going through it" and something has traumatised me now because I just... I've ALREADY done the fucking fighting. I've pushed. I've tried to advocate for myself so many times
What was the point in making myself stick around and do that if I'm just gonna give up now???

For all the fucking shit I've fought for in the past and all the shit I pushed through and forced myself to stay alive through, I'm not allowed to give up, because I could have just saved myself the pain and given up sooner.

I feel like every single time in my life I have been given reprieve and started finding hope and purpose it has been ripped out from under me and I am so stubborn because I've made it this far and I want to keep fighting
But at the same time I guess those moments don't erase the damage I've felt either.

And I honestly... Barely feel like I have ever caught a break. It literally feels like my life is trauma after trauma and I know that's not 100% true, I know that I have felt so many moments of insurmountable joy
I just.. I feel like I've already grieved for a lot of stuff I've lost and I feel like I have to do it all over again and like I'm losing more and more
I don't wanna commit to the idea that this is my life from here on out.
Like... I don't wanna give myself false hope by insisting that this is just my body recovering and it'll go away one day
I'm tired of being tired and in pain literally every day 🙂 it was bad enough before 🥲 and it's just constant now. It's really hard to um... Try to keep my thoughts balanced and realistic

Do I start with a YouTube channel? Do I start with a dedicated blog? Do I try to look into grants for something? Do I try to find people who are already in advocacy for input, and where do I even find them?
There are so, so many things I want to do, and so many huge dreams I have, but I do not know what it realistic and what is too ambitious.
I am also hyper aware about the fact that I don't want it to be something that takes away from my ability to care for myself as well.
I don't even know where to start. I don't know think writing zines is enough for me in this respect. I think this needs to be something I do with other people rather than just myself

that feels like it matters, I want to share knowledge and advice and normalise this shit and help reduce shame. And I want it to be bigger than me, I want it to be a job or something that I can't articulate right now while I'm ~down with the sickness~
